      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, every CommandLineFlag has an implied \u0027-\u0027 in front of it when it gets rendered (see the []string below, which is how it will be rendered).\n\nWith the exception of --help and --version, all python (and python3) flags are short-form (e.g. `-V`), so dropping the \u0027-\u0027 from everything makes sense. This also prevents us from needing to add \u0027-\u0027 when we parse a CLI which combines many short ops together (like `-vm pip` is `[(\"v\", \"\"), (\"m\", \"pip\")]` instead of `[(\"-v\", \"\"), (\"-m\", \"pip\")]`)",
